President Trump and Italian Prime Minister Giuseppe Conte held a joint press conference at the White House. They announced a new strategic dialogue between Italy and the United States that will enhance cooperation on various issues, including joint security efforts in the Mediterranean and combating terrorism and uncontrolled migration. Both leaders emphasized the need for strong border security and discussed their shared goal of preventing Iran from obtaining a nuclear weapon. They also addressed trade and commerce, with President Trump mentioning a recent breakthrough agreement with the European Union to remove trade barriers and increase US exports. The leaders expressed their desire to strengthen the economic relationship between their countries. They also discussed the importance of reducing regulations and promoting economic growth. President Trump expressed his willingness to meet with Iranian President Rouhani without any preconditions if Iran is ready for negotiations. The press conference also touched on issues such as sanctions on Russia, energy production in Libya, and Italy's involvement in the F-35 program.